name: Isabel Bader Centre For The Performing Arts
directions: Single, gender neutral washroom on first floor (bottom floor, below entry level), along the back hallway of the building. Ask the front desk for directions, the building can be confusing to navigate.
comment: The building is open weekdays 8am-5pm, and occasionally on the weekend and/or in the evening during events. If you're not comfortable asking someone for directions, the gendered multi-stall washrooms on the second (entry level) floor are easier to find and rarely have anyone in them during the day. From walking in the front door, turn right, go past the front desk, turn right again and follow the hallway until you find them.

name: Renne Library
directions: Once inside past the Borrow Desk you can take the elevator on the left or the stairs to the right up to the third floor. Once on the third floor there are two quiet areas on either side. The quiet area through the glass doors without the large fountain and the green carpet will have the restroom. Once in that area turn right and continue along the wall and just past the lounge chairs and coffee table it will be to your right again. There are two push to turn on lights and the door locks.
comment: The library is open to both students, faculty and staff, as well as community members. Just go upstairs but you can browse around the library or get coffee. On the second floor up the stairs and to the left there is a pleasant LGBTQ section in the HQ stacks. Sappho is located on the third floor in the fountain quiet area, I like Mary Bernard's translation (PA4408.E5B37)
